{{Abortion-stub}}

In both South and North [[Yemen]], abortion is only performed to save the mother's life. This is in accordance with [[Islamic law]] (which generally prohibits abortion).<ref>{{cite web |title=Yemen |url=http://www.un.org/esa/population/publications/abortion/doc/yemen.doc |publisher=United Nations |accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref> Yemen has the highest birth and mother mortality rate in the Middle East.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mamoon |first1=Amal |last2=al-Sakkaf |first2=Nasser |title=Abortion in war time: How women break taboos in Yemen |url=https://www.middleeasteye.net/news/abortion-yemen-how-women-break-taboos-during-war-time-1098650760 |website=Middle East Eye |accessdate=24 August 2018 |language=en |date=27 April 2017}}</ref>

