{{Orphan|date=February 2012}}
{{Infobox organization | name = Fight Forever Foundation | founded_date = 2006 | founder = Danny Ferrone | location = [[Park Ridge, Illinois]] | origins = | key_people = | area_served = Worldwide | focus = [[Cystic fibrosis]] | method = | revenue = | title =Fight Forever Foundation | endowment = | num_employees = | owner = | Non-profit_slogan = "Find a Cure or Die Trying" | homepage = [http://fightforever.org fightforever.org] }}
The '''Fight Forever Foundation''' is a [[501(c)3]] [[non-profit foundation]] founded to find a cure for [[cystic fibrosis]](CF), a life-threatening, genetic lung disease affecting 100,000 people worldwide. This objective is expressed in both Danny's personal mission and the shared mission of the Foundation, "Find a Cure or Die Trying." To accomplish this mission the Foundation continues to build their International Medical Advisory Board to collectively stay abreast of the evolving advancements being made for a cure, while simultaneously raising funds, to effectively support promising advancements.
==History==
Danny Ferrone was diagnosed with cystic fibrosis at the age of two.<ref name="diagnosis">{{cite web| url =http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1N1-11AA3FB250FA5FE0.html| title =LFHS graduate Ferrone gives all to find cystic fibrosis cure| publisher =High Beam Research| accessdate =2009-08-12}}</ref> After three and a half years weathering the harsh winters and high altitude of Colorado while a student at the University of Denver, Danny returned home to Chicago to focus on his health. While training for the 2006 Accenture Triathlon, Danny came up with the idea to create the Fight Forever Foundation. Founded by Danny Ferrone and two of his close friends, the Foundation's immediate fundraising efforts were centered on a campaign which involved Danny competing in triathlon and marathon events which were supposed to culminate in the [[Ironman World Championship]] in Kona, Hawaii in 2008. Danny, with his limited lung capacity around 50%,<ref name="lung capacity">{{cite web| url =http://abclocal.go.com/wls/story?section=news/local&id=5694060| title =Chicago man with cystic fibrosis running in marathon for cure| publisher =ABC 7 News| accessdate =2009-08-12}}</ref> finished marathons in Las Vegas, Los Angeles, and Chicago, and the Accenture Triathlon in Chicago, twice, over the two-year campaign. However, his goal of qualifying for the Ironman World Championship fell short after a hard-fought performance at the qualifying Buffalo Springs Lake triathlon event in Lubbock, Texas in June 2008, where his time of 5 hours, 48 minutes failed to land him a spot in Kona.<ref name="Lubbock">{{cite web| url =http://www.lubbockonline.com/stories/063008/spo_297531338.shtml| title =At Buffalo Springs Lake, Chicago native shows why he's an iron man| publisher =Lubbock Online| accessdate =2009-08-12}}</ref>
==Current projects== Never willing to give in, Danny is currently in Milan, Italy working together with the Italian Cystic Fibrosis Research Foundation and researchers throughout Europe, while continuing his training to compete in more marathons and triathlons. He regularly speaks internationally at seminars for both researchers and people living with CF where he discusses the "Battle" he faces on a daily basis, and provides support to families and individuals also battling the disease.
