{{Infobox dam | name = Ivaylovgrad Dam | image = Ivaylovgrad-dam-wall.jpg | image_caption = Ivaylovgrad Dam | dam_crosses = [[Arda (Maritsa)|Arda River]] | location = 13 km north-west of [[Ivaylovgrad]] / [[Haskovo Province]], [[Bulgaria]] | dam_type = Concrete gravity dam | dam_length = {{convert|250|m|ft|abbr=on}} | dam_height = {{convert|73|m|ft|abbr=on}} | plant_hydraulic_head = {{Convert|52|m|abbr=on}} (Max) | spillway_type = fixed-crest, overflow spillway at two levels | spillway_capacity ={{convert|5250|m3/s|ft3/s|abbr=on}} | construction_began = 1959 | opening = 1964 | cost = | owner = [[NEK EAD]] | operator = NEK EAD | res_name = [[Ivaylovgrad Reservoir]] | res_capacity_total = {{convert|157000000|m3|acre.ft|abbr=on}} | res_catchment = {{Convert|5128|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}} | res_surface = {{Convert|15.2|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}} | plant_operator = NEK EAD | plant_turbines = 4 x [[Francis turbine|Francis-type]] | plant_capacity = 104 [[megawatt|MW]] | plant_annual_gen = 195 [[GWh]] | location_map = Bulgaria | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|41|32|2|N|26|6|27|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} }}
The '''Ivaylovgrad Dam'''(язовир "Ивайловград") is located in the eastern [[Rhodope Mountains]] and is situated on the [[Arda (Maritsa)|Arda]] river, Southern Bulgaria. There are another two large dams of the Arda upstream - [[Kardzhali Dam]] and [[Studen Kladenets|Studen Kladenets Dam]] to the west of Ivaylovgrad Dam.
The dam creates [[Ivaylovgrad reservoir]], which has a total volume of {{convert|157000000|m3|acre.ft|abbr=on}} and a [[drainage basin]] of {{convert|5128|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}. It is situated at an average 120 m above sea level, its dam being {{convert|250|m|ft|abbr=on}} long and {{convert|73|m|ft|abbr=on}} high. The top of the dam consists of six spillways, totaling {{convert|83.5|m|ft|abbr=on}} m in length.<ref>[http://www.ebrdrenewables.com/sites/renew/Lists/Projects/DispForm.aspx?ID=1773&Source=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eebrdrenewables%2Ecom%2Fsites%2Frenew%2Fcountries%2FBulgaria%2Fdefault%2Easpx Ivailovgrad Hydro Power Plant]</ref><ref>[http://www.nek.bg/cgi?d=1434 NEK brochure "Hydro Power Casdaces and Dams" page 36] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706143239/http://www.nek.bg/cgi?d=1434 |date=2011-07-06 }}</ref>
Ivaylovgrad Reservoir is an attractive place for tourists and [[fishing|fishermen]], where [[rudd]] is caught in great numbers.
==Hydroelectric generation== Arda Hydro Power Cascade consist of three large hydro power sites, mainly used for electricity generation, with a total installed capacity of 331 MW and a total annual output of over 520 GWh/y. Ivaylovgrad [[hydroelectric power plant]] (HPP) is the last stage of the Arda cascade. The initial plans for the construction of a dam on the Arda date to as early as 1948. Construction began in 1959 and was completed in 1964, with the HPP starting production the same year. "Ivaylovgrad" Hydroelectric Power Plant is built-in inside the dam. The HPP has four [[Francis turbine|Francis-type turbines]], 26 [[megawatt|MW]] each with a mean annual generation of 195 GWh/y.
